value.0: This winged beauty has silky soft and pure skin, and the smile on her face makes you feel at ease.
Behlin wandered from his mountain home, injured, and was nursed back to health by a concerned druid. In return, he prowls his new home, keeping his senses alert for trespassers.

Danger is an extremely large male wolf, most likely a pack leader.  He peers at you cautiously, knowing one false move on your part would mean his next meal.  Scars of recent and long forgotten battles mar his face and neck.
Dewdrop is one of the sires in the pack.  She looks almost as fiercesome as Danger, and almost as large.
One of the younger females of breeding age, Destiny competes with Dewdrop for Danger's affections.
Oldest of the pack pups, Dusk spends most of his time trying to do everything Danger does.
Effectively a runt, Dall struggles to keep up with the other wolves, but his determination is admirable.

The Great Duir is the most sacred of trees held holy by all Druids.  It is rumored to be almost as old as the land itself, and Druids will defend this tree with their life.  It is the root of all existance to them.  Stories have been told of the Great Duir's long roots, digging deep into the ground and suckling life from The Mother directly.

It is rumoured that an ancient god, Taranis, would come down from the skies and mate with the Great Duir by striking it with lightning.  This is how he came to be known as the Thunder Lord.  Druids are known to carry pieces of lightning-blasted Duir as a symbol of protection, love, and mating.

As you stand under this enormous tree you feel a presence here - as if the tree itself were aware of you and watching over you.  As the wind blows through the leaves, a faint song can be heard that is relaxing and somewhat hypnotizing.
